import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='incidents')
    
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='incidents', data=data)
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the trend of the number of incidents reported during the LA riots?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    incident_counts = data['incident_type'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(incident_counts, labels=incident_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the type of incidents reported?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
